                <head>No. 83.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Low</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-05-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 21, 1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 81]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your No. 130, of 5th of
                    February, inclosing a copy of a correspondence between yourself and Viceroy Li
                    Hung Chang, upon the subject of sending to the United States a number of Chinese
                    youths to be educated, I have to request you to inform the viceroy that I will
                    gladly render such counsel and advice in the matter as may be in my power.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
